tx-swr32: Dark Flaring & Methane Emissions
==========================================

Identifies unpermitted ("dark") flaring and potential venting in the
Permian Basin by cross-referencing public datasets:

  1. SWR 32 exception permits — scraped from the Texas RRC
  2. RRC well locations — parsed from EBCDIC bulk data files (wellbore,
     P-4 Schedule for current operators, P-5 organizations)
  3. VIIRS Nightfire — satellite-detected flares from EOG/NOAA
  4. Carbon Mapper — hyperspectral methane plume detections (Tanager-1)
  5. IMEO/MARS — multi-satellite methane plumes (UNEP)


Dark flaring analysis
---------------------
Spatially matches satellite flare detections to nearby wells (1km),
then checks whether those wells had valid SWR 32 exception permits at
the time of detection. Permit matching uses both spatial (GPS of
permitted flare locations within 1.5km) and operator-based methods.
Follows Earthworks "benefit of the doubt" methodology.


Methane plume analysis
----------------------
Cross-references methane plume detections with VNF flare sites to
identify potential venting (unlit flares). Each plume is classified as:

  - unlit:     near a known flare site, no thermal detection (+-1 day)
  - flaring:   near a known flare site, thermal detection confirmed
  - wellpad:   near a well, but no known flare infrastructure
  - unmatched: not near any well in our data

Plumes are attributed to operators via the same well-matching pipeline
as the flaring analysis.


Setup
-----
Requires: uv, duckdb CLI, Playwright (chromium)
Optional: EOG account for VNF data (credentials in .env)
Optional: IMEO GeoJSON from methanedata.unep.org (save as data/imeo_plumes.geojson)

  uv sync
  uv run playwright install chromium


Usage
-----
  make db          Full pipeline: parse, load, analyse
  make plumes      Fetch latest CM + IMEO plume data
  make refresh     Rebuild database from current CSVs
  make build       Build Observable notebook
  make preview     Local dev server
  make clean       Remove derived data (keeps raw downloads)

  duckdb data/dark_flaring.duckdb    Query results interactively


Key tables
----------
  dark_flares         Daily VNF detections with permit status
  plume_attributed    Plumes with well/operator/VNF cross-reference

Key views:
  dark_flaring_summary   Aggregate dark flaring stats
  top_dark_flares        Top unpermitted flare sites by radiant heat
  plume_summary          Plume counts by classification and source
  unlit_flares           Plumes at flare sites with no thermal signal
  top_plume_operators    Operators ranked by methane emissions


Known limitations
-----------------
- Gas well district mismatch: P-4 uses districts 09/10 for Permian gas
  wells while wellbore completion records use 07/08. Only ~20% of wells
  have type 21 bridge records connecting the two systems.
- SWR 32 permits in our data start Oct 2023; flare GPS coverage starts
  ~Q2 2025 and is still backfilling.
- ~60% of methane plumes are "unmatched" — likely midstream facilities
  (compressor stations, gathering systems) not in our wells database.
